The article is a statement by the President on the House passage of the Food Safety Enhancement Act of 2009. The legislation aims to raise food safety standards, give the FDA the power to issue mandatory recalls of harmful products, and improve oversight of imported food. The President sees this as a major step towards modernizing the food safety system and protecting Americans from foodborne illness. He commends the House of Representatives for passing the bill and looks forward to working with the Senate to enact it into law.